A group, Abubakar Bukola Saraki (ABS) Contact and Advocacy Committee of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has met with the state working committee of the Kano State chapter, urging party faithful to ensure that former Senate President Bukola Saraki emerges as the party’s presidential candidate. Senator Iyorwuese Hagher, who led the group, described Saraki as a young, well-educated, experienced, honest and committed leader who has the capabilities to lead the country. Soldiers must return to barracks – CISLAC Ondo returns schools to missionaries 46 years after The PDP chairman in Kano, Shehu Wada Sagagi, urged aggrieved party members to shun unfavourable acts and embrace open discussions in addressing contending issues.